1. What is popup?
- Popup is an UI element that appears on the top of the main page to take user input or show information. It can be:
    - Window popup
    - Alert popup
    - Modal popup

2. What are the types of popups in selenium?
- Types of popups:
    - Browser window popups
    - JavaScript alert popup
    - HTML modal popup
    - Authentication popup

3. Can Selenium handle all types of popups directly?
- No , Selenium can handle:
    1. Alerts , YES (switch_to_alert)
    2. Window , YES (switch_to_window)
    3. Modal , YES (normal DOM elements)
But OS-level popups -> Not directly supported

4. What is a window popup?
- A window popup is when clicking a link/button opens a new browser window/tab 

5. How does Selenium identify multiple windows?
- Using driver.window_handles

6. How do you switch between windows in Selenium?
- Using
    driver.switch_to_window(window)

7. What is a window handle?
- A unique ID assigned by the browser to each window/tab

8. How do you switch back to the main window?
- main_window = driver.current_window_handle
- driver.switch_to_window(main_window)

9. How do you handle multiple windows?
    main = driver.current_window_handle

    for handle in driver.window_handles:
        if handle != main:
            driver.switch_to.window(handle)
            break

10. How do you wait for a new window to open?
- Use explciti Wait (WebDriverWait)

    WebDriverWait(driver , 10).until(EC.number_of_window_to_be(2))

11. What is a modal popup?
- A modal popup is an HTML element displayed over the page without opening a new window

12. How do you handle modal popup in Selenium?
- We handle it like normal elements:
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "username").send_keys("test")
- No Switching required

13. Difference between window popup and modal popup?
Feature & Window Popup & Modal Popup
------------------------------------
- Type -> Browser window popup , Normal HTML modal 
- Switching needed -> YES , NO
- Selenium method -> switch_to_window , normal locators
- DOM presence -> separate , same page

14. What happens if you don’t switch to a new window?
- Selenium will throw exception
    NoSuchElementException

15. How do you switch window by title?
    from window in driver.window_handles:
        driver.switch_to_handle:
            if "Google" in driver.title:
                break

16. What is the difference between driver.close() and driver.quit()?
- driver.close() -> used to close current window
- driver.quit() -> close all browser windows

17. How do you handle dynamic window popups in real-time?
- Steps:
    - Store main window
    - trigger action
    - wait for new window
    - switch to new window
    - perform action
    - close child window
    - switch back

18. Can modal popup be handled using switch_to.window?
- NO , Because modal popup is part of DOM, not a separate window

19. How do you handle authentication popups in Selenium?
- Selenium cannot handles OS level popups directly
- Solution : URL Injection
    driver.get("https://user:pass@site.com")

20. What is a real-time example of window popup in testing?
- Payment gateways (PayPal, Razorpay)
- Social login (Google login)
- Ads opening in new tab

21. What is the biggest challenge in window handling?
- Multiple windows opening unpredictably
- Sitching to current window
- Synchroizatoin issues

22. How do you ensure you are in the correct window?
- Checj:
    - Title
    - URL
    - Element presence
    assert "Dashboard" in driver.title

23. What happens if window closes and you try to switch back?
- You will get:
    NoSuchWindowException

24. How do you handle multiple tabs opened automatically?
    for handle in driver.window_handles:
        driver.switch_to_handle(handle)
Then validate each.

25. Can Selenium interact with hidden modal popups?
- YES , but only after:
    - Waiting for visibility
    - Using explicit wait

26. Window opens but Selenium still cannot find elements. Why?
- Because , you did not switch to new window

27. Modal popup is visible but click fails. Why?
- Possible reasons:
    - Overlay not fully loaded
    - Element not clickable
    - Need explicti wait

28. How do you debug window handling issues?
- Print window handles
- print titles
- Use screenshots
- Use explcit waits

